## [2026-03-17] PI-01: Authorized UI Framework Deviation

### The Pivot
Bypassing the mandated v2026 `Eldora UI` and web-runtime architectures in favor of the `CustomTkinter` Python library for the Application GUI.

### The Rationale
This project is bound by the "Featherweight" constraints. The end-users are senior financial accountants operating heavily restricted, legacy office hardware (older OS versions, <= 4GB RAM). 

Modern native web runtimes (like Electron, Tauri, or Bun-backed web views) carry a massive memory footprint that would cause these legacy machines to freeze or crash when running concurrently with massive Excel ledgers.

`CustomTkinter` ensures we can build a safe, native, strictly Python-based cross-platform executable that looks semi-modern but has an incredibly lightweight footprint. This pivot guarantees absolute stability and zero memory thrashing for the financial accounting demographic.
